📖 Theory
What is a Filesystem?

A filesystem organizes data on storage devices.

Common Linux filesystems:

ext4
xfs
btrfs
Block Devices

List disks:

lsblk

Example:

NAME   SIZE TYPE MOUNTPOINT
sda    100G disk
├─sda1   1G part /boot
└─sda2  99G part /
