🔥 Production Scenario

Problem: A Jenkins server has stopped working because the root filesystem is full.

Investigation
df -h

Check large directories:

sudo du -sh /var/*

Find the biggest files:

sudo find / -type f -size +100M

Clean logs (only after verifying they are safe to remove or rotate):

sudo journalctl --vacuum-time=7d

Remove unused packages:

sudo apt autoremove
sudo apt clean

Verify free space:

df -h
🧠 Senior DevOps Challenge

Write a script called storage-monitor.sh that:

Checks disk usage.
Warns if any filesystem exceeds 80% usage.
Displays the top 10 largest directories under /var.
Shows inode usage.
Saves the report to storage-report.txt with a timestamp.

Bonus: Exit with a non-zero status code if any filesystem exceeds 90%, making it suitable for monitoring or CI/CD checks.

